TITLE: Triggering a Novu Workflow via API
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to make an API call to trigger a Novu workflow event. The request includes the workflow trigger identifier, subscriber ID, and payload data needed for the notification process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/novuhq/docs/blob/main/content/docs/platform/concepts/workflows.mdx#2025-04-11_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
curl -X POST https://api.novu.co/v1/events/trigger \
  -H "Authorization: ApiKey <NOVU_SECRET_KEY>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "<WORKFLOW_TRIGGER_IDENTIFIER>",
    "to": {
      "subscriberId": "<UNIQUE_SUBSCRIBER_IDENTIFIER>",
    },
    "payload": {}
  }'
```

