TITLE: Implementing Reference and Reuse in JSON Schema
DESCRIPTION: This schema demonstrates how to define reusable component definitions and reference them throughout a schema. It includes address components that are reused for billing and shipping, and a recursive node structure for hierarchical data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/novuhq/docs/blob/main/content/docs/framework/schema/json-schema.mdx#2025-04-11_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "definitions": {
    "address": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "street_address": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "city": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "state": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      "required": ["street_address", "city", "state"]
    },
    "node": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "name": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "children": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "$ref": "#/definitions/node"
